# Caddy front door for Boss.
#
# Single virtual host driven by the `BOSS_HOSTNAME` env var.
# Caddy terminates HTTPS via Let's Encrypt (HTTP-01 by default —
# the host must resolve directly to your VM's IP, no proxy in
# front). Reverse-proxies to boss-gateway on 127.0.0.1:4443.
#
# Usage: set BOSS_HOSTNAME and run `caddy run --config Caddyfile`
# (or use the unit installed by infra/caddy/setup.sh, which
# reads /etc/boss/caddy.env). For local dev without a public
# hostname, point BOSS_HOSTNAME at `localhost` and Caddy will
# serve over HTTP.
#
# Cloud-provider-specific recipes (Cloudflare Tunnel + Origin
# Certificate, AWS ALB termination, GCP HTTPS LB) used to live
# here as a second virtual host pinned to the project's old
# playground deployment. The 2026-05-06 cloud-provisioning rip
# moved those recipes to a future "Cloud provider blueprints"
# Post-release item — see TODO.md.

{$BOSS_HOSTNAME} {
    encode gzip

    reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:4443 {
        # Needed for Server-Sent Events to stream without buffering.
        flush_interval -1
    }

    log {
        output stdout
        format console
    }
}
